Quote:  [sc wool], Gilbert was kept busy assisting to bale the wool, which was removed from the bins to the wool-press, where it was carefully packed and tightly pressed into the compact bales which might be adopted as emblematic of the wealth of the Australian colonies, as the woolsack was that of Britain.
